Offline-build support for iox_query_udf (InterGenOS packaging).

When the env var IOX_QUERY_UDF_STAGED_DIR is set, the build script looks
for pre-fetched wasm-binary artifacts there before attempting the network
download. Candidates are checksum-verified against the same sha256 the
build script would use to validate a fresh download; mismatches fall
through to the original download path. When the env var is unset,
upstream behavior is preserved exactly.

This lets the cargo build complete inside an offline chroot where the
upstream GitHub-releases download would fail with DNS-lookup errors.
The fetch_artifact() function is the only change; all download /
checksum / panic-on-mismatch logic remains intact.

Apply with: patch -p0 (paths are anchored relative to the influxdb
source root).

--- core/iox_query_udf/build.rs
+++ core/iox_query_udf/build.rs
@@ -66,6 +66,21 @@
         return target_file;
     }

+    // OFFLINE-BUILD SUPPORT (InterGenOS packaging):
+    // If IOX_QUERY_UDF_STAGED_DIR is set, look for the artifact there first
+    // and copy it into the cargo OUT_DIR location if it matches the expected
+    // checksum. This allows building inside an offline chroot where the
+    // upstream download would fail with DNS lookup errors. When the env var
+    // is unset, upstream behavior (network download) is preserved exactly.
+    if let Ok(staged_dir) = std::env::var("IOX_QUERY_UDF_STAGED_DIR") {
+        let staged = PathBuf::from(&staged_dir).join(name);
+        if staged.exists() && sha256(&staged) == checksum {
+            std::fs::copy(&staged, &target_file)
+                .expect("failed to copy staged artifact to OUT_DIR");
+            return target_file;
+        }
+    }
+
     // build timestamp in URL has a specific format:
     // - the TZ offset is not included (it's always UTC anyways)
     // - since `:` doesn't work in URLs, `-` is used
